ui.clui

Class CommandLineController

  • java.lang.Object
    • ui.clui.CommandLineController

  • public class CommandLineController
extends java.lang.Object
    This class contains all the methods that can be used in the command line. Every methods take String[] arguments in order to be compatible with CommandLineReader.parseArgs(String).
    Author:
    Pietro Dellino

    • Constructor Summary

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Concrete Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      void addBike(java.lang.String[] args)
      This method applies command line instructions of the form:
      addBike <networkName> <type> <time>
      or
      addBike <networkName> <stationID> <type> <time> The time has to be on the following format: YYYY-MM-dd HH:mm The type has to be electric or mechanic.
      void addSlot(java.lang.String[] args)
      This method applies command line instructions of the form:
      addSlot <networkName> <stationID> <numSlots>
      void addStation(java.lang.String[] args)
      This method applies command line instructions of the form:
      addStation <networkName> <type> <numSlots> <positionX> <positionY>
      The type has to be stardard or plus.
      void addUser(java.lang.String[] args)
      This method applies command line instructions of the form:
      addUser <username> <cardType> <networkName>
      The type has to be vlibre, vmax or credit.
      void calculateItinerary(java.lang.String[] args)
      This method applies command line instructions of the form:
      calculateItinerary <networkName> <userID> <startX> <startY> <destinationX> <destinationY> <pathStrategy>
      The pathStrategy can be minimal-walking, fastest-path, prefer-plus, avoid-plus, or uniformity.

        public void rentBike(java.lang.String[] args)
              throws InexistingNetworkNameException,
                     InexistingUserIdException,
                     InexistingStationIdException,
                     NegativeTimeException,
                     InvalidArgumentsException,
                     OngoingRideException,
                     NoBikeAvailableException,
                     StationOfflineException,
                     NoElectricBikeAvailableException,
                     NoMechanicBikeAvailableException
        This method applies command line instructions of the form:
        rentBike <userID> <stationID> <bikeType> <time> <networkName>
        The time has to be on the following format: YYYY-MM-dd HH:mm The type has to be electric or mechanic. The case is ignored. The type is optional, if it is not written, any bike will be rented.
